2. Revenue Threshold and Commercial License Requirement

If Direct Software Revenue exceeds USD 100,000 in any consecutive
twelve (12) month period, you must obtain a separate commercial license
from the Licensor in order to continue using, distributing, or
commercially exploiting the Software.

Continued use of the Software without a commercial license after
exceeding the revenue threshold constitutes a material breach of this
license and results in automatic termination of the rights granted
herein.

3. Definition of Direct Software Revenue

"Direct Software Revenue" means revenue received in exchange for access
to, use of, or rights in the Software itself, including, without
limitation:

(a) Sale or licensing of the Software;
(b) Paid subscriptions or usage fees where the Software is the primary
    product or service;
(c) Hosting, SaaS, or managed service offerings where the Software
    itself is the primary value delivered;
(d) Paid add-ons, extensions, or enhancements that directly modify or
    extend the Software.

Direct Software Revenue expressly excludes:

(a) Revenue from products, services, or businesses that merely use the
    Software as an internal tool, dependency, library, or development
    aid;
(b) Revenue from unrelated or downstream products developed using the
    Software;
(c) Consulting, integration, customization, or support services where
    the Software is not sold or licensed as a standalone product;
(d) General business revenue not directly attributable to access to the
    Software itself.

